  "title": "Sales Manager (Analytical Instruments)",
  "description": "<p>Responsiblilities:<br /></p><ul><li>Achieving Orders and Sales target, YOY growth and margin across all analytical product lines</li><li>Develop sales strategies to build opportunities including researching and identifying new business opportunities (existing and new accounts); building strong rapport; providing technical information and clarifying customers’ doubts if any; configures and prepares quotations as well as closing deals.</li><li>Practice key account management skills – Taking accountability and ownership of accounts assigned. Includes scheduling customers’ visits, understanding customers’ pain points, facilitating\napplication problems solving with internal teams, and coordinating pre- and post-sales activities.</li><li>Practice sense of urgency and escalate issues early if any.</li><li>Understand market trends and build knowledge on competitive offerings. </li><li>Responsible for sales activities to meet the sales goals and develop new prospects including penetration into competitive accounts.</li><li>Accountable for CRM data hygiene - Setup, maintain, monitor, and cultivate accurate customer information and sales\nopportunities in SFDC in an organized timely manner. </li><li>Prepare and deliver presentations through face-to-face visits / seminars to address customers’ business needs by accurately positioning PerkinElmer solutions </li><li>Bring back information for internal discussion, strategize and create business plans.</li><li>Work closely with internal applications, service teams and product line leaders and provide good customer support. </li><li>Submit accurate and timely sales forecasts. </li><li>Develop business plans through quarterly plans of action.</li></ul><p><br />Requirements:<br /></p><ul><li>Bachelor's Degree or Masters in Chemistry </li><li>At least 5-8 years of sales experience in Analytical instruments e.g. Chromatography, inorganic, material characterisation equipment</li><li>Have own transport and willing to travel if required</li></ul><p><br />Account Manager:<br />Kerwin Tan Kai Bin (R1331624)<br />kerwin.tan@searchasia.com.sg<br />EA16S8107</p>",
